                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Went off to a meeting and lunch after posting.  Seems you took my post rather antagonistically.  It wasn't intended that way.<br /><br />Currently, due to the LDoN testing going on, /bug on Test and Beta is read a lot more than normal.  On Test it's actually read a lot, and quicker than most folks think.  However, it's a matter of priority.  Priority of X bug might be huge for one person, but for the devs it might be much lower.  Long time Test necros remember when illusions caused the entire zone to lag out, so skellie & Lich form was useless as people would scream at you for it.  I remember one dev I chatted at for a while...guy was so stressed from trying hard to get everything fixed to make everyone happy he worked himself sick, literally.  Several others work hours you'd not believe.  But don't expect them to drop everything and fix the problem 20 minutes after you submit it.<br /><br />As for last night and today, no patch has been loaded to Test since last night.  I was on until late last night, and I jumped on this morning early to try and catch Mercyy before heading to work.  No patch, so code should be the same.  Be sure when you /bug you specify which pet as well.  My 63 and 65th pets were working fine - it might be your specific one that has issues, or, possibly, something in the zone itself.  Bug reports now automagically grab your location when you bug them due to so many people sending bug reports of "I'm standing here and blah blah isn't happening, pls help".  It's possible that it's part of the current issue list Test's code has.  <br /><br />If you watched pet for 17 minutes and it regened 3% health, something is obviously wrong.  I'm going to assume you basically walked away or read a book or something and didn't fight a thing in that timeframe, which would of course contribute to health loss.  Did you try dropping the pet and resummoning?  Silly solution, but hey, you never know.  On Test, wacky code is legendary.  I could tell you stories about code I've seen over the past 4 years that you'd swear I was making up.<br /><br />To conclude, expect strange things and times on Test.  Expect the server to drop 5 seconds before you can loot item_you've_camped_for_years.  Expect rollbacks.  Expect bad code.  Test isn't for those wanting to camp solo, Test is for the people who are willing to endure the pain so that other servers won't have to.  The few things that slip through are inconsequental to what doesn't.  /bug your problem, and try to work around it.  It will get fixed.</span id="msg"></font></td>
