                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Ancient: I'll go out on a limb and throw my lot in with Rekcim as I've been part of this dicussion at least 3 times now. Pre Kunark and durring every expansion after there have been people that claim their pets regen more when sitting and bring it up here. People think that because 1. Something in the original documentation says something like it. 2. PCs regen more sitting down then so must pets. This of course as we all know is NEVER true. PCs and NPC play off vastly different rules. That said lets go trough a very easy and quick test for this.<br /><br />Bring up a pet and get it beat to shit. Spam the pet health button every couple of seconds and make note of what % health the pet has for each and every tick up to 100%. Repeat this at least 3 times so that people dont bitch at you for not testing enough. Do the same test only this time sit the pet down before taking any readings. <br /><br />I'll bet you'll find that the % of health gained will be virtully the same for each and every test. I think the most that you are going to see is something like 3% 3% 3% 4% 4% 3% 3% 3% with a bit of varience based on the life the pet started with. (note actually % may vary!) <br /><br />The pets have never seemed to gain anything from sitting. It has never for me added any significant amout to the pets regen.</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
